Claude may:

1. Search for existing theme utilities.
2. Identify shared layout components.
3. Review CSS framework configuration.
4. Plan the implementation.
5. Add a theme provider.
6. Update reusable components.
7. Add a toggle to the header.
8. Test the application.
9. Verify color contrast and consistency.
10. Summarize the completed work.

Again, the task involves multiple iterations of the Agentic Loop.

