# 16. Best Practices

* Write prompts that clearly define the goal.
* Allow Claude to gather context before expecting code changes.
* Review intermediate results when working on critical features.
* Let Claude verify its work by running tests whenever possible.
* Treat Claude as a collaborative engineer rather than an infallible automation tool.

---

# 17. Common Mistakes

* Providing vague prompts that force unnecessary exploration.
* Interrupting Claude before it has completed its verification steps.
* Assuming the first iteration is always the final solution.
* Ignoring the value of test execution and verification.

