# 17. Understanding the Working Directory

One of the most important concepts is the **working directory**.

Claude only has access to the directory where it is launched and its subdirectories.

Example:

```text
Projects
│
├── BankingApp
│
└── PlaywrightFramework
```

If you run:

```bash
cd BankingApp
claude
```

Claude can access:

```text
BankingApp/

src/

tests/

package.json
```

It **cannot** access:

```text
PlaywrightFramework/
```

unless you start Claude from that directory.

---

## Why This Matters

This design improves:

* Security
* Privacy
* Project isolation

