claude
```

Claude can access **every project** inside Workspace.

Sometimes this is useful.

Often, it is not.

Instead:

```bash
cd Automation
claude
```

Now Claude only sees:

```text
Automation/

tests/

pages/

utils/

package.json
```

This keeps Claude focused and reduces unnecessary context.

---

## Best Practice

Always launch Claude from the **root directory of the project you're actively working on**.

