# 7. Writing Better Prompts

Let's compare prompts of increasing quality.

---

### Poor

```text
Fix bug.
```

---

### Better

```text
Fix the login bug.
```

---

### Good

```text
The login API returns HTTP 401 after users reset their passwords.

Investigate only the authentication service.

Run authentication tests afterward.
```

---

### Excellent

```text
The login API returns HTTP 401 after password reset.

Investigate only the backend authentication flow.

Do not modify frontend code.

If configuration changes are required, explain why before making them.

Run the authentication test suite after implementation.

Provide a summary of the root cause and every modified file.
```

Notice how each improvement reduces ambiguity.

---

# 8. Prompt Patterns for Common Development Tasks

## Understanding a New Codebase

```text
Explain the overall architecture of this project.

Describe each major folder.

Explain how requests flow through the application.
```

---

## Investigating a Bug

```text
The checkout page throws a 500 error after payment.

Investigate the backend.

Identify the root cause.

Do not implement a fix yet.

Explain your findings.
```

---

## Implementing a Feature

```text
Add Dark Mode to the application.

Reuse the existing theme utilities.

Persist the user's preference.

Do not modify authentication.

Run the UI tests after implementation.
```

---

## Refactoring

```text
Refactor duplicate validation logic.

Avoid changing external behavior.

Keep existing tests passing.

Explain the design improvements.
```

---

## Writing Tests

```text
Generate Playwright tests for the login flow.

Cover:

- Successful login
- Invalid password
- Locked account
- Session timeout

Use the existing Page Object Model.
```

---

# 9. Prompt Chaining

Large tasks are easier when divided into smaller prompts.

Instead of asking:

```text
Rewrite the entire application.
```

Use a sequence.

---

### Step 1

```text
Explain the authentication architecture.
```

---

### Step 2

```text
Identify weaknesses.
```

---

### Step 3

```text
Create an implementation plan.
```

---

### Step 4

```text
Implement the approved plan.
```

---

### Step 5

```text
Run tests and summarize the changes.
```

Prompt chaining keeps Claude focused and reduces errors.

---

# 10. Good vs Bad Prompt Examples

| Poor Prompt  | Better Prompt                                                       |
| ------------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Fix it       | Fix the login bug in the authentication service.                    |
| Add feature  | Add Dark Mode to the customer dashboard.                            |
| Explain      | Explain the payment flow from API request to database.              |
| Improve code | Refactor the validation module without changing behavior.           |
| Write tests  | Generate Playwright tests for checkout using existing page objects. |

