# 11. When to Skip a Phase

Not every task requires all four stages.

| Task                | Explore | Plan     | Code     | Commit   |
| ------------------- | ------- | -------- | -------- | -------- |
| Explain a file      | ✅       | ❌        | ❌        | ❌        |
| Find a bug          | ✅       | Optional | Optional | ❌        |
| Rename a variable   | ❌       | ❌        | ✅        | Optional |
| Large feature       | ✅       | ✅        | ✅        | ✅        |
| Architecture change | ✅       | ✅        | ✅        | ✅        |
| Documentation       | ✅       | Optional | ✅        | Optional |

As a rule:

* Small changes can often skip planning.
* Large or architectural changes should always follow the full workflow.

