# 17. Chapter Summary

The Context Window is Claude Code's working memory and is one of the most important concepts to understand when working with AI coding agents. Everything Claude reads, every command it runs, every file it analyzes, and every conversation you have contributes to the available context.

Because the context window is finite, Claude automatically compacts older information into summaries as needed. Developers can also manage context manually using `/context`, `/compact`, and `/clear`, ensuring that Claude remains focused and efficient throughout long development sessions.

By understanding how context grows and how to manage it, you'll be able to work on larger projects without losing continuity or wasting valuable context.

