# 2. Why Context Management Matters

Imagine you're working for six hours on a Playwright automation framework.

During those six hours Claude has:

* Read 150 files
* Executed 40 commands
* Read thousands of log lines
* Generated hundreds of code edits
* Answered dozens of questions

Eventually Claude's memory begins filling up.

When this happens:

* Responses become slower.
* Claude may forget small implementation details.
* Claude begins summarizing previous conversations.
* Exploration becomes less efficient.

Proper context management prevents these issues.

---

# 3. Signs That Your Context Is Becoming Too Large

