# 13. How MCP Servers Affect Context

MCP (Model Context Protocol) servers extend Claude with external tools, but they also affect context.

Every enabled MCP server contributes:

* Tool definitions
* Available commands
* Metadata

Even if you don't use them immediately.

---

## Example

Suppose you enable:

* GitHub MCP
* Jira MCP
* AWS MCP
* Slack MCP
* Database MCP

Each adds information to Claude's available context.

If many servers are enabled but unused, they consume space unnecessarily.

---

## Best Practice

Enable only the MCP servers relevant to your current project.

We'll cover MCP in detail in Chapter 16.

