# 14. Best Practices

✅ Let Claude decide when to use built-in Subagents.

✅ Use Explorer for investigation tasks.

✅ Use Plan Mode for architecture changes.

✅ Create custom Subagents for repetitive workflows.

✅ Use Subagents to reduce context usage on large projects.

✅ Keep custom Subagents focused on a single responsibility.

---

# 15. Common Mistakes

### ❌ Expecting Subagents to Persist

Subagents disappear after completing their work.

Only the summary remains.

---

### ❌ Using One Subagent for Everything

Create specialized Subagents.

Don't build a "does everything" agent.

---

### ❌ Forgetting That Subagents Have Separate Context

They don't automatically know the entire conversation unless Claude passes relevant information.

---

### ❌ Overengineering Custom Subagents

Keep them focused.

Examples:

Good:

* Security Reviewer

* Performance Reviewer

Bad:

* Universal Everything Agent

