# 14. Exit Codes

The course explains an important concept for **PreToolUse Hooks**.

Hooks communicate success or failure using **exit codes**.

| Exit Code | Meaning            |
| --------- | ------------------ |
| **0**     | Continue execution |
| **2**     | Block execution    |

---

## Example

Claude wants to execute:

```bash
rm -rf src
```

Hook:

```text
Detect rm -rf

↓

Exit Code 2

↓

Block Command
```

Claude receives the reason the command was blocked and can adjust its behavior.

