# 💼 Hooks for Your Playwright / WDIO Automation Framework

Given your work in **Playwright, WDIO, Appium, BrowserStack, and API testing**, these Hooks would be especially useful:

| Hook                   | Action                                                                                     |
| ---------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| **PostToolUse (Edit)** | Run `npm run lint` after every code edit.                                                  |
| **PostToolUse (Edit)** | Run `prettier --write` on modified files.                                                  |
| **PostToolUse (Edit)** | Execute `tsc --noEmit` to catch TypeScript errors early.                                   |
| **PostToolUse (Edit)** | Run only the affected Playwright tests (where feasible).                                   |
| **PreToolUse**         | Block deletion of `playwright.config.ts`, `wdio.conf.ts`, or critical framework files.     |
| **PreToolUse**         | Prevent `git push --force` or deletion of test directories.                                |
| **Stop Hook**          | Display a desktop notification when long-running test generation or refactoring completes. |
| **UserPromptSubmit**   | Log prompts for team auditing or knowledge sharing.                                        |

These automations help enforce consistent quality across your automation framework while reducing manual effort.

