# 1. Introduction

After learning every individual feature of Claude Code, it's time to put everything together.

Many developers install Claude Code and immediately start asking it to write code.

While this works, it's **not the most effective way** to use an AI coding agent.

The course emphasizes a structured workflow that helps Claude:

* Understand your project
* Plan before coding
* Verify its work
* Produce higher-quality implementations

Instead of treating Claude like a chatbot, you should treat it like a **junior software engineer** that collaborates with you.

---

# 2. Why a Workflow Matters

Consider two developers.

### Developer A

```text
Open Claude

↓

Write feature

↓

Fix bugs

↓

Rewrite

↓

Fix again

↓

Commit
```

Result:

* More bugs
* More corrections
* Wasted context
* Slower development

---

### Developer B

```text
Explore

↓

Plan

↓

Approve

↓

Code

↓

Verify

↓

Review

↓

Commit
```

Result:

* Fewer mistakes
* Better architecture
* Cleaner code
* Less rework

The second approach is the one recommended throughout the course.

